<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5723375>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. An adult female of Pulvinaria kuwacola Kuwana, 1907, on the twig of Cornus florida." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5723375/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5723379>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Pulvinaria kuwacola Kuwana, 1907, adult female collected from Fukuoka prefecture in 2021. ANT, antenna: AP, anal plate; DA, dermal areolation; DMD, dorsal microduct; DS, dorsal seta; DTD, dorsal tubular duct; LG, leg; MP, multilocular pores; MS, marginal seta; POP, preopercular pores; SDP, spiracular disc pore; SSP, stigmatic spines; VMD, ventral microduct; VTD, ventral tubular ducts, types I to III. Scale bars: 200 μm for ANT, DA and LG, 100 μm for AP, 50 μm for MS and SSP, and 10 μm for all other features." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5723379/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

